description: Dee-Dee gets the birthday present of her dreams in "Dee-Dee's Pony Tale", but it's, well, a real Trojan horse. Plus, Dexter tries to take a scientific shortcut while playing miniature golf!
name: Dee-Dee's Pony Tale; Miniaturized Golf

description: Dexter hangs up his lab coat for some truly deadly duds in "Dexter's New Clothes." Plus, Dee-Dee and Dexter hunt for homework in a haunted house.
name: Dexter's New Clothes; Spook House

description: Three new stories have Dexter using mad science in brand new ways. First, he does the impossible and makes toys...that come with batteries. Then he creates a device to get his gloves on the TV remote--and another to stop himself from humming the catchy (but annoying) ditty in his head.
name: Doot-Doot-Doot!; Control Freaks; Time On My Side

description: How's a kid to keep soup from dribbling down his shirt? If you're a super-genius like Dexter, all you need to do is create a super-spongey spoon. But when Dee-Dee ends up swiping it, Dexter gets himself in a world of trouble.

When Mandark shrinks himself to literally find the way to his true love's heart, Dexter gets sucked into the action--and into Dee-Dee. Plus, Dexter bids big money on a Tyrannosaurus Rex in "Auction Action!"
name: Head Trip!

description: In order to become a better ShadowHawk, Eddie decides to speak with the ShadowHawks of the past, and learns a thing or two about being a true hero.

description: The internationally acclaimed best-seller is now finally presented in English! Meet Noa, a so-called Sky Doll; a life-like female android without rights, who exists only to serve the State's needs and desires. But when Noa meets two so-called 'missionaries' who aid in her escape from her tyrannical master, all hell breaks loose for our cyborg siren as she uncovers clues that she may be much more than just a robotic toy.
name: La Ville Jaune

description: In sky doll 2, Noa and her friends go to the water planet Aqua. As the Papess' planet is filled with Catholic imagery, the planet Aqua is full of 1960's era designs. The religion seems to be a satire of Scientology, but also holds more: the population is entirely female and all clones. Noa, who revealed she has 'something' within she does not understand, gets a souvenir of her trip and comes close to losing her pet Scrope (a white animal, somewhat like a possom with a ball on its tail and another for a nose. All of the Scropes look alike and all seem connected in some way--and Noa's can talk.)
name: Aqua

description: Now Noa is really in trouble. The Miracle Genii wants her, Lodovica is furious, her Scrope is up to something and the two guys get in a fight. Plus, Flora Decibel and her daughter, on their news satellite, are making their own fun.
name: La Ville Blanche

description:
Man has battled the undead for millenia. Best-selling author Max Brooks provides the lessons that history has taught us about zombie outbreaks as he chonicles the most famous outbreaks, gruesomely illustrated in graphic novel form. From our descendants on the African savannahs to the legions of ancient Rome, from the voyages of Francis Drake to the ill-advised experiments of the Soviet army, The Zombie Survival Guide: Recorded Attacks takes the reader on a journey across many anni horribilis and hauntingly reminds us how close the living dead have come to destroying humanity.

Back Blurb

Those who don't learn from history are condemned to repeat it.

From the Stone Age to the information age, the undead have threatened to engulf the human race. They're coming. They're hungry.

Don't wait for them to come to you!

This is the graphic novel the fans demanded: major zombie attacks from the dawn of humanity. On the African savannas, against the legions of ancient Rome, on the high seas with Francis Drake... every civilization has faced them. Here are the grisly and heroic stories -- complete with eye-popping artwork that pulsates with the hideous faces of the undead.

Organize before they rise!

Scripted by the world's leading zombie authority, Max Books, Recorded Attacks reveals how other eras and cultures have dealt with -- and survived -- the ancient viral plague. By immersing ourselves in past horror we may yet prevail over the coming outbreak in our time.

Chapter Titles

  • 60,000 B.C., Katanda, Central Africa
  • 3000 B.C., Hieraconpolis, Egypt
  • A.D. 121, Fanum Cocidi, Caledonia
  • A.D. 1579, The Central Pacific
  • A.D. 1583, Siberia
  • A.D. 1611, Feudal Japan
  • A.D. 1690, The Southern Atlantic Ocean
  • A.D. 1862, St. Lucia, Eastern Caribbean
  • A.D. 1893, French North Africa
  • A.D. 1942-45, Harbin, Japanese Puppet State of Manchukuo
  • A.D. 1960, Byelgoransk, Soviet Union
  • A.D. 1992, Joshua Tree National Park

The third book by Max Brooks, Recorded Attacks is the first graphic novel that recounts early zombie vs. humans events in the history of the world.
name: Recorded Attacks
